Package: scSidekick
Title: A Single-Cell and Spatial Transcriptomics Toolkit
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person(given = "Nourhan",
           family = "Abdelfattah",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "neabdelfattah@gmail.com")
Description: A toolkit for single-cell RNA-seq, spatial transcriptomics,
    and bulk expression analysis. Provides enhanced visualization functions
    (dot plots, UMAP grids, feature maps, spatial plots), a custom
    ggplot2 theme and color palettes, GSEA pathway analysis wrappers,
    CellChat pipeline wrappers, and utility functions for extracting
    methods text from Seurat objects. Also includes a Kaplan-Meier survival
    analysis module (SurvPlot) that accepts bulk expression matrices or
    downloads TCGA datasets automatically, supports gene-level and
    gene-set-signature stratification, flexible High/Low or quartile
    splitting per facet group, and row x column faceting by clinical
    metadata variables. Also includes a PowerPoint summary builder
    (PDFs → PPTX via officer/magick), a passive session logger that
    auto-captures commands and plots, and a rule-based session summarizer
    that generates a markdown report and a clean R script.
    Designed to work seamlessly with Seurat.
